    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-01T18:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-01T18:53:00-05:00" n="839"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/7–154: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 839<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d839fn1">Repeated to Amman <gloss target="#t_niact1"
                            >niact</gloss>, London, Paris, and Jerusalem, and by pouch to the Arab
                        capitals and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-01T19:53:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1954—7:53 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Deliver following message Jordan (Israel) Government soonest: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>US Government has been informed widespread heavy firing broke out in
                            Jerusalem June 30<note n="2" xml:id="d839fn2">Reports concerning the
                                outbreak of firing in Jerusalem were contained in telegrams 1 and 3
                                from Jerusalem, 2 and 5 from Tel Aviv, and 1 from Amman, all dated
                                July 1. (684A.85/7–154)</note> and has since continued
                            intermittently, reportedly having been resumed even after agreement on
                            cease fire reached at meeting Israel–Jordan Mixed Armistice Commission
                            July 1. US Government deplores this serious outbreak violence in Holy
                            City with attendant loss of life and urges Government Jordan (Israel)
                            take immediate steps insure observance cease fire. US Government
                            transmitting identical request Government Israel (Jordan).</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
